# Migration from JasperReports (JRXML) to Thymeleaf + OpenHTMLToPDF

## Executive Summary

The migration from JasperReports to Thymeleaf + OpenHTMLToPDF was initiated primarily to address PDF accessibility (WCAG/PDF-UA) requirements and improve long-term maintainability.

A review of the existing reporting implementation revealed that JasperReports is primarily being used as a document layout engine rather than leveraging advanced reporting capabilities such as native charts, crosstabs, or report designers.

The proposed solution standardizes report generation on commonly used web technologies (HTML, CSS, Thymeleaf) while simplifying accessibility implementation and reducing technical complexity.

---

# Current Architecture

```text
Business Data
      ↓
Java Processing
      ↓
BufferedImage / Drawable Generation
      ↓
Jasper Image Objects
      ↓
JRXML Template Rendering
      ↓
PDF Export
```

## Observations

### 1. Limited Usage of Jasper-Specific Features

Analysis of approximately 250+ JRXML templates indicates:

- No usage of Jasper chart components
- No usage of crosstabs
- No usage of advanced report designer capabilities
- No dynamic report-building features

Graphical content is currently generated programmatically within Java and injected into reports as images.

Example:

```text
Java Code
    ↓
Generate BufferedImage
    ↓
Pass through imageExpression
    ↓
Render inside JRXML
```

Therefore, JasperReports is primarily functioning as a document rendering layer.

---

### 2. Accessibility Challenges

Implementing PDF accessibility requirements within JRXML templates has proven difficult.

Challenges include:

- Complex accessibility tagging
- PAC validation failures
- Additional workarounds for semantic document structure
- Limited alignment between JRXML and modern accessibility standards

---

### 3. Specialized Skill Requirements

Current solution requires knowledge of:

- JRXML
- Jasper Studio
- Jasper Expressions
- Jasper-specific layout concepts

These skills are not commonly shared across development teams.

---

# Proposed Architecture

```text
Business Data
      ↓
Java Processing
      ↓
