## 6. Reduced JVM Heap Utilization

### Current Approach

```text
Drawable
    ↓
BufferedImage
    ↓
Stored within Jasper object model
    ↓
PDF Export
```

Characteristics:

- Large in-memory image objects
- Increased heap usage
- Potential GC pressure during report generation

### Proposed Approach

```text
Drawable
    ↓
Temporary SVG File
    ↓
Referenced by HTML
    ↓
PDF Rendering
    ↓
Temporary File Deleted
```

Characteristics:

- Lightweight SVG resources
- Reduced memory retention
- Graphics externalized to filesystem
- Lower heap pressure

### Business Value

Improved scalability for image-heavy reports.

---

